h3. Summary
When an user is viewing the backlog of a kanban board that has issues from more than 1 project, the quick filter affect what is displayed in the "versions" panel.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a kanban board;
# Edit the filter to return multiple project;
# Map a status or more to the backlog;
# Click on the backlog;
# Click on any Quick Filter;

h3. Expected Results
* The versions panel should allow you to view all versions (scrum board as example).

 !Scrum board versions panel.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Actual Results
* The versions panel is affected by the Quick Filter.

 !Kanban board versions panel.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Workaround(s)
* There is none.

h3. Summary
Epics from other projects are being displayed when the Epic Link drop-down menu is selected (even though projects are using different issue type schemes)

h3. Steps to reproduce

# Login to JIRA as an Administrator;
# Create an Epic in a project;
# Now create a new issue and choose a different project;
# Click on the dropdown of the "Epic Link" field;
# Epics from different projects are being listed in the same list as Epic from the current  project;

h3. Expected Results

The Epic Link drop-down menu should contain only Epics from the current project

h3. Actual Results
Epics from multiple projects are being displayed on the list 
